post_text:
REOPENING UPDATE: August 28, 2020

Dear Sussex Tech families,

Thank you for your patience and understanding as we have finalized our reopening plans with your students’ teachers in school this week. We have a new Q&A page on our website to answer many of the questions that you have. It covers topics including scheduling, grading, textbooks, services, technology, and much more.

You will also be receiving a copy of this Q&A and other information in the mail next week. If you have a question which is not answered there, please email feedback@sussexvt.k12.de.us and we will get you an answer.

We are greatly looking forward to the start of school, and hope you are also. From all of us at Sussex Tech, please stay safe and be well.

SENIOR PHOTOS - IMPORTANT DEADLINE:

Seniors, if you have not already had your senior yearbook picture taken, please email Ms. Vadnais immediately at nicole.vadnais@sussexvt.k12.de.us for an appointment time. *These appointments must be kept.* We have no more time to reschedule appointments so that seniors can be included in the regular portrait section of the yearbook. Our last day to photograph seniors for the senior section is October 9. Any photos taken after October 9 will be included in a separate section of the yearbook. If you have any questions, email Ms. Vadnais at nicole.vadnais@sussexvt.k12.de.us.

On this Labor Day, we celebrate our students who are learning their chosen fields and becoming prepared for their future - whether that's career, college, or military service.

We thank and honor our teachers and staff for helping and guiding them along their paths. Our team puts students first each and every day, from maintenance staff to teachers, counselors to climate officers.

And we congratulate our thousands of alumni, who are applying their Tech educations and working hard each and every day.

#RavenPride #TechTough

❓❓❓ This week, we’re sharing questions and answers about our reopening plan. You can find all the answers at the link below!

QUESTION: How will I get notifications or find out news from Sussex Tech?

ANSWER: We know it is important for families to stay in touch with their students’ schools, which is why we offer information in multiple ways.
> We have a call-home system which can leave a recorded message on your voicemail and a messaging system which sends messages directly to your email. Please check your voicemail regularly, and add us to your safe sender email list.
> We also post all communications on our website, sussexvt.org, and on our social media channels (Facebook, Twitter and Instagram).

QUESTION: How can I make sure that Sussex Tech has our household’s most current contact information?

ANSWER: If you haven’t received any calls or emails from us since early August, please contact the high school at 302-856-0961 to make sure we have your family’s current information on file.

❓❓❓ This week, we’re sharing questions and answers about our reopening plan. You can find all the answers at the link below!

QUESTION: What precautions are Sussex Tech taking to protect students and staff from COVID-19?

ANSWER: The health and safety of our students and staff is our highest priority. We are taking every recommended precaution, and our leadership talks regularly with the Division of Public Health and the Delaware Department of Education. Precautions for anyone on campus include:
* Mandatory mask-wearing
* Social distancing
* Daily temperature checks
* Regular cleaning and disinfecting of high-contact surfaces throughout the day
* Deep cleaning on a nightly basis

TEXTBOOK RETURNS —> We are holding textbook returns next week:

• Seniors on Wednesday, August 26
• Juniors on Thursday, August 27
• Sophomores on Friday, August 28

Please bring your textbooks to school between 10 a.m. and 2 p.m. on those dates. Please park your vehicles in the main bus parking lot near the gym, and have your students take their books to tables on the sidewalk. Staff members will be able to assist. All textbooks and materials will be sanitized at the end of each day before going back into classrooms. Students should wear masks. Students can also have the opportunity to enter the school, escorted by staff, and clean out their lockers at this time.

This does not apply to calculators.

If you cannot stop by on your assigned day, please call the high school office to leave a detailed message with a call-back number at 302-856-0961.

DISTRICT CLOSED TO HONOR JUNETEENTH: The Sussex Technical School District, high school, and school grounds will be closed tomorrow, Friday, June 19, to allow employees time to honor Juneteenth.

Juneteenth is recognized annually to celebrate the reading of federal orders proclaiming that all enslaved persons in the U.S. state of Texas were free. It is a date to celebrate freedom and also serve as a reminder that the promise of equity is a constant struggle.

Our offices will reopen Monday.

Because of the inclement weather forecast, the graduation ceremonies scheduled for Thursday have been rescheduled to Saturday:

>> 10 a.m. Saturday, June 13 - Health Professions; Dental Services; Media Broadcasting

>> Noon Saturday, June 13 - Digital Publishing & Design; Business, Finance and Marketing; Cisco Networking; Carpentry; Physical Therapy – Athletic Health Care

Families should arrive an hour before the event – at 9 a.m. for the 10 a.m. ceremony, and at 11 a.m. for the noon ceremony.

We regret the short notice, but Saturday has excellent weather forecast. The long-term forecast for our original rain date is uncertain, and we did not want to have to cancel the ceremony a second time.

** Please note that Friday’s graduation ceremonies will go ahead as planned. **

Please email feedback@sussexvt.k12.de.us if you have any questions.

BAND EQUIPMENT UPDATE

Students enrolled in Band and issued a uniform and/or instrument:

You may bring these items to drop off at the school on June 3 and 5 from 4:30 p.m. - 6:30 p.m. in A parking lot (the bus parking lot nearest the gym entrance).

Ms. Batten and band volunteers will stay 10 feet or more away from visitors except when retrieving uniforms and instruments from vehicle windows or trunks. All visitors parents/students shall stay inside their vehicles.

There will be five stations set up in the parking lot for different items. As you drive through each station, you will hand the items to a volunteer through the car window or leave your trunk unlocked.

If you have any questions, please call the main office at 302-856-0961 and leave a detailed message with a callback number or email your teacher.

During this difficult time, Sussex Tech students have been supporting our front-line health care heroes. Freshman Nacesseca Cherazard and sophomore Callie Goff each have created handmade thank-you cards and messages for staff at Sussex County hospitals.

“It was something I felt that I needed to do,” said Cherazard, who made the cards for staff at Beebe Healthcare. Goff, who made the cards and snack bags for staff at Nanticoke Memorial Hospital, said, “I thought it would be nice to give back to the people who have given so much to us.”

Thanks to our Ravens for helping others fly!

post_text:
QUILTS OF VALOR: During the fall semester, 15 student and staff volunteers joined the Quilts of Valor team to contribute to their quilts honoring veterans. Most students were new to quilting, but once given a quick lesson they were off and running. Here's what they produced!

These two blocks still need to be sewn and top-stitched to complete the quilts, and will be donated to a local veteran. The group plans to continue quilting again next year, and will be working on a special black, gray and silver quilt to be auctioned off and profits going to Quilts of Valor to support the cost of materials.

Thanks to the great volunteers who helped with this amazing effort!

A message for Sussex Tech students who use the Wellness Center:

The Wellness Center staff want you to know that even though school is not in session, we are here for you. If you have questions or concerns about your health or follow-up appointments or just want to talk, please reach out to us at 302-855-1233. Identify yourself as a Sussex Tech student and our staff will assist you.

We want to provide you with the same level of service here at La Red that we provide to you at the Wellness Center. If you require a visit, we will be happy to see you at our location at 21444 Carmean Way, Georgetown.

Unfortunately, we cannot see new patients at this time, and services are only for students who are currently being seen at Wellness.

If you are experiencing fever, shortness of breath, cough, sore throat or any other flu like symptoms, please call your primary care provider as soon as possible. Stay safe and stay healthy.

post_text:
Today is International Haiku Poetry Day, and some of our teachers contributed a few poems ... enjoy!

From Dr. Carmen (Electronics):
Electrons do work
Moving our information
So kids can still learn

From Mrs. Collins (Spanish):
“¡Hola muchachos!
¿Cómo están ustedes?”
I miss my students.

From Mrs. Gehrke (Digital Publishing & Design):
Draw, Write, Sing, Dance, Laugh
Paint your toe nails with teal hearts
Just Stay Creative

From Mr. Collins (Mathematics):
Numbers
Are paintbrushes for earth.
Math is how we understand the picture.

And from Dr. Neal:
So we are apart
Family is love and strength
We can handle this!
